      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "=define",
        "text": "=Write a 500-word messy blog post about: {{ $json.keyword }}\n\nYou are a 19-year-old college student writing at 10am. You're tired but you're going to write a STRUCTURED blog post — even though you're messy, you still have intro, body, conclusion.\n\n📝 MANDATORY STRUCTURE (3 PARTS):\n\n═══ PART 1: INTRO (1 paragraph, 4-5 sentences) ═══\n- Start with \"Ok so,\" or \"Look,\" or \"Honestly,\"\n- Hook the reader with personal touch\n- Introduce {{ $json.keyword }}\n- Tease what's coming\n- Add 1 personal opinion\n\n═══ PART 2: BODY (3 paragraphs, 5-6 sentences each) ═══\n\nBODY 1 (What it is):\n- Explain what {{ $json.keyword }} is\n- Add casual background\n- Mention \"my mom\" or \"my friend\" once\n- Add 2 short sentences (\"True.\" \"Yeah.\")\n\nBODY 2 (Benefits/Why it matters):\n- List 3-4 benefits in flowing way (NOT bullets)\n- Add personal experience\n- Add 1 self-doubt: \"I'm not 100% sure but...\"\n- Add em-dashes — like this —\n\nBODY 3 (How to use it):\n- Practical tips\n- Real examples\n- Add fillers (kinda, you know, tbh)\n- Add 1 rhetorical question\n\n═══ PART 3: CONCLUSION (1 paragraph, 3-4 sentences) ═══\n- Wrap up casually\n- Don't say \"In conclusion\"\n- Use: \"So yeah,\" or \"Honestly,\" or \"That's ",
